---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Projects - Steve Wang"
  description="Selected projects by Steve Wang, including digital signage CMS work, Fuel Tracker, the hosted Shared Bill web app, Project Status Hub, and purchasing workflow tooling."
  current="projects"
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-title section-wrap">
      <h1>Projects</h1>
      <p>
        Selected work across full-stack product development, live personal software,
        private operations dashboards, and purchasing workflow automation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section-wrap project-list">
      <article class="detail-card" id="digital-signage-cms">
        <div class="detail-header">
          <div>
            <span class="project-meta">Full-stack product</span>
            <h2>Digital Signage CMS</h2>
          </div>
          <span class="status-label">Production work</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Scope</h3>
            <p>Production CMS for digital signage content, screens, assets, templates, editing, permissions, billing, and deployment workflows.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Owned Work</h3>
            <p>Permission control, Stripe payment setup, related CMS flows, CI/CD pipeline work, backend APIs, database changes, and production support.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Also Supported</h3>
            <p>CRM sync, screen monitoring notifications, Electron support, and Android/Tizen TV app maintenance.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tech Stack</h3>
            <p>React, TypeScript, Node.js, MySQL, Stripe API, Ontraport CRM, Docker, Nginx, CircleCI, Bitbucket Pipelines, AWS EC2.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="detail-card" id="fuel-tracker">
        <div class="detail-header">
          <div>
            <span class="project-meta">Live tool</span>
            <h2>Fuel Tracker</h2>
          </div>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="https://fueltracker.stevewang.me">Open tool</a>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Problem</h3>
            <p>Fuel records are easier to keep when receipt details can be captured quickly and reported flexibly.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Solution</h3>
            <p>A personal fuel logging app with AI receipt extraction, built for quick data entry, cost tracking, and flexible reporting.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>AI Extraction</h3>
            <p>Litres, pump unit price, retail total, fuel grade, brand, station name, and purchase datetime.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tech Stack</h3>
            <p>Web app, AI API integration, AWS Amplify deployment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="demo-strip" aria-label="Fuel Tracker screenshots">
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/fueltracker-overview.png" alt="Fuel Tracker overview showing consumption, cost, distance, and recent activity." loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Overview metrics and recent activity</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/assets/fueltracker-ai-entry.png" alt="Fuel Tracker add-fill screen showing AI receipt extraction filling fuel details." loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>AI-assisted receipt entry</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="detail-card" id="shared-bill">
        <div class="detail-header">
          <div>
            <span class="project-meta">Live web app</span>
            <h2>Shared Bill</h2>
          </div>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="https://sharebill.stevewang.me">Open app</a>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Purpose</h3>
            <p>Hosted app for recording shared expenses, splitting costs, and calculating who should pay whom.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Web Migration</h3>
            <p>Completed React/Vite web migration with Supabase-backed sign-in, groups, invites, shared bill storage, and completed transfer tracking.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Import Path</h3>
            <p>Owner-only desktop JSON import keeps the original Electron data path useful while moving shared records into the hosted backend.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tech Stack</h3>
            <p>React, Vite, Supabase Auth, Supabase Postgres, AWS Amplify Hosting, Electron, shared settlement logic, and unit/UI tests.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="detail-card" id="project-status-hub">
        <div class="detail-header">
          <div>
            <span class="project-meta">Private dashboard</span>
            <h2>Project Status Hub</h2>
          </div>
          <span class="status-label">Owner-only</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Purpose</h3>
            <p>Private operations dashboard for personal web projects, covering deploy health, uptime, provider status, collector errors, aggregate usage, and month-to-date cost.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tracked Apps</h3>
            <p>Personal Hub, Shared Bill App, Fuel Tracker App, and Project Status Hub itself.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Access Model</h3>
            <p>Frontend login gates the dashboard before data renders, and Supabase RLS allows reads only for approved authenticated dashboard users.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tech Stack</h3>
            <p>Vite web app, Supabase Auth, Supabase row-level security, scheduled collectors, AWS Amplify Hosting, and GitHub-based branch deployment flow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="detail-card" id="purchasing-workflow-tools">
        <div class="detail-header">
          <div>
            <span class="project-meta">Current focus</span>
            <h2>Purchasing Workflow Tools</h2>
          </div>
          <span class="status-label">In progress</span>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Goal</h3>
            <p>Speed up low-stock ordering decisions that can be done in Excel, but take longer to prepare and check manually.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Current Tool</h3>
            <p>Python import flow for item, sales, cost, price, and supplier data with automatic order amount calculation.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Rules</h3>
            <p>Uses supplier MOQ, layer price, pallet price, and packaging constraints when calculating suggested order amounts.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tech Stack</h3>
            <p>Python first. Future UI will depend on the workflow shape after the calculation model is stable.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
